<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
    <title>Icecream</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <link href="/css/pure-min.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
    <link href="/css/base-min.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
    <link href="/css/icecream.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
    <script src="/js/config.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/index.js"></script>
    <script>
      document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
        Index(iConfig);
      });
    </script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="header" class="pure-g">
      <div class="pure-u-2-24 logo">
        <img id="logo" class="pure-img" src="/images/icecream-small.png" />
      </div>
      <div class="pure-u-22-24 title">
        <span id="titleHeader"></span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="main-content" class="pure-g">
      <div class="pure-u-1">
        <p class="intro">Welcome to <strong>icecream</strong>, a web-based live video broadcaster.</p>

        <p><a class="pure-button pure-button-primary" href="/broadcast.html">Get started now</a></p>

        <p class="large">With <strong>icecream</strong> you can live stream your workshops, key note speakers, personal performances or anything you can capture on your web camera.</p>

        <p>So what are you waiting for? Fix your hair and <a href="/broadcast.html">start streaming!</a></p>

        <p class="small"><em><strong>Icecream</strong> is a html5-based Icecast video source client. That means it can capture your video and audio from your webcam and microphoe and send that video and audio to an <a href="https://icecast.org">Icecast server</a> which then broadcasts it to the world. You can't use <strong>icecream</strong> without an Icecast server. <strong>Icecream</strong> can only capture video via Chrome/Chromium versions 47 and higher and Firefox versions 25 and higher (since it uses the <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaRecorder">MediaRecorder API</a>). Watching streams is supported in Firefox (4 and higher), Chrome/Chromium (6 and higher), Opera (10.6 and higher), and seems to be supported in some versions of Internet Explorer and Edge. It seems impossible to view on an iPad or iPhone and only with a struggle in Safari. <strong>Icecream</strong> source code is available via <a href="https://gitlab.com/jamie/icecream">gitlab</a>. </em></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
